cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about developing a more efficient and accurate sentence encoder specifically optimized for dialog tasks in conversational AI applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The use of pretrained representations and transfer learning also suggests cs.LG (Learning) as a possible sub-category. The paper involves retrieval-based response selection, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of quantization and subword-level parameterization suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible sub-category.
